      "question_number": 1,
      "question_text": "What is simple harmonic motion (SHM)?",
      "attempted": 2,
      "data_i18n": null,
      "options": [
        {
          "text": "Periodic motion with restoring force proportional to displacement: F = −kx",
          "is_correct": true,
          "data_i18n": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Any periodic motion",
          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Motion in a circle",
          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Motion at constant speed",
          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        }
      ],
      "explanation": "Displacement is the straight-line distance from start to finish with direction (vector). It differs from distance, which is the total path length (scalar). The answer is 'Periodic motion with restoring force proportional to displacement: F = −kx'. The other options — 'Any periodic motion', 'Motion in a circle', and 'Motion at constant speed' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question."
    },
    {
      "question_number": 2,
      "question_text": "What is the period of a mass-spring system?",
      "attempted": 2,
      "data_i18n": null,
      "options": [
        {
          "text": "T = 2π√(m/k)",
          "is_correct": true,
          "data_i18n": null
        },
        {
          "text": "T = 2π√(k/m)",
          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        },
        {
          "text": "T = mk",
          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        },
        {
          "text": "T = 2πmk",
          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        }
      ],
      "explanation": "Hooke's Law: F = -kx, where k is the spring constant and x is displacement from equilibrium. Elastic PE = ½kx². The answer is 'T = 2π√(m/k)'. The other options — 'T = 2π√(k/m)', 'T = mk', and 'T = 2πmk' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question."
    },
    {
